[It now appears in this expanding ongoing outbreak that red onions are the vehicle for transmission of the salmonellosis. The contamination of the produce may have been in the field or during or after harvesting.

Anecdotally, here in northwest Wisconsin where I work as an infectious diseases physician, we currently have 3 inpatients with salmonellosis, 2 of whom had bacteremia. The strains are to be evaluated and sent to the CDC but may well be part of this growing outbreak. - Mod.LL

